cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.GT 

The paper deals with optimizing the transmission strategies of secondary users in a cognitive radio network, which involves network protocols, information theory, and system optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses tools from stochastic geometry, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with system optimization, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper uses numerical evaluations, which falls under cs.MA (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with optimization problems, which falls under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
